cpwVcAtmMIB.name: cpwVcAtmMIB
cpwVcAtmMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS Email: cs-atm@cisco.com
cpwVcAtmMIB.description: This MIB contains managed object definitions for Pseudo Wire emulation of ATM over Packet Switched Networks(PSN). This MIB reports to the PW-MIB. The PW-MIB contains structures and MIB associations generic to Pseudo-Wire Virtual Circuit (VC) emulation. VC-specific MIBs (such as this) contain config and stats for specific VC types.

cpwVcAtmTable.name: cpwVcAtmTable
cpwVcAtmTable.description: This table specifies the information for an ATM interface, VC, VP to be carried over PSN.

cpwVcAtmEntry.name: cpwVcAtmEntry
cpwVcAtmEntry.description: A row in this table represents an ATM interface, VC, VP that needs to be adapted and carried over PSN. This table is indexed by CpwVcIndex in CISCO-IETF-PW-MIB.

cpwAtmIf.name: cpwAtmIf
cpwAtmIf.description: The ATM Interface that receives cells from the ATM network.

cpwAtmVpi.name: cpwAtmVpi
cpwAtmVpi.description: VPI value of this ATM VC.

cpwAtmVci.name: cpwAtmVci
cpwAtmVci.description: VCI value of this ATM VC.

cpwAtmClpQosMapping.name: cpwAtmClpQosMapping
cpwAtmClpQosMapping.description: This Object indicates whether the CLP bits are considered when determining the value placed in the Quality of Service fields (e.g. EXP fields of the MPLS Label Stack) of the encapsulating protocol.

cpwAtmRowStatus.name: cpwAtmRowStatus
cpwAtmRowStatus.description: This Object is used to create, modify or delete a row in this table.

cpwAtmOamCellSupported.name: cpwAtmOamCellSupported
cpwAtmOamCellSupported.description: This Object indicates whether OAM Cells are transported on this VC.

cpwAtmQosScalingFactor.name: cpwAtmQosScalingFactor
cpwAtmQosScalingFactor.description: This Object represents the scaling factor (% value) to be applied to ATM QoS rates when calculating QoS rates for the PSN domain . For example, in the cell transport mode the bandwidth needed in the PSN domain will be higher (since PSN Transport header, PW header, and optional control word have to transmitted with every cell), whereas in the AAL5 mode the bandwidth needed in PSN domain will be less since cell headers will be removed after reassembly.

cpwAtmCellPacking.name: cpwAtmCellPacking
cpwAtmCellPacking.description: This object is used to identify if the VC is configured to do Cell Packing.

cpwAtmMncp.name: cpwAtmMncp
cpwAtmMncp.description: This object indicates the maximum number of cells that get packed in one packet.

cpwAtmPeerMncp.name: cpwAtmPeerMncp
cpwAtmPeerMncp.description: This Object represents the maximum number of cell that can be packed in one packet for peer interface.

cpwAtmEncap.name: cpwAtmEncap
cpwAtmEncap.description: This object indicates if the packet going on the pseudowire is mpls or l2tpv3 encapsulated.

cpwAtmMcptTimeout.name: cpwAtmMcptTimeout
cpwAtmMcptTimeout.description: This Object represents which MCPT timeout value.

cpwVcAtmPerfTable.name: cpwVcAtmPerfTable
cpwVcAtmPerfTable.description: This table specifies performance-related attributes for an ATM vc, vp and the interface.

cpwVcAtmPerfEntry.name: cpwVcAtmPerfEntry
cpwVcAtmPerfEntry.description: A row in this table represents an ATM interface, VC, VP that needs to be adapted and carried over PSN. This table is indexed by CpwVcIndex in CISCO-IETF-PW-MIB.

cpwAtmCellsReceived.name: cpwAtmCellsReceived
cpwAtmCellsReceived.description: This object can be used to obtain the information on the number of cells that were received and sent to the PSN.

cpwAtmCellsSent.name: cpwAtmCellsSent
cpwAtmCellsSent.description: This object can be used to obtain the information on the number of cells that were received from the PSN and sent over the ATM network.

cpwAtmCellsRejected.name: cpwAtmCellsRejected
cpwAtmCellsRejected.description: This Object indicates the number of cells that were rejected by this VC because of policing.

cpwAtmCellsTagged.name: cpwAtmCellsTagged
cpwAtmCellsTagged.description: This Object indicates the number of cells that were Tagged.

cpwAtmHCCellsReceived.name: cpwAtmHCCellsReceived
cpwAtmHCCellsReceived.description: High Capacity counter for the number of cells that were received by this VC.

cpwAtmHCCellsRejected.name: cpwAtmHCCellsRejected
cpwAtmHCCellsRejected.description: High Capacity counter for the number of cells that were rejected by this VC because of policing.

cpwAtmHCCellsTagged.name: cpwAtmHCCellsTagged
cpwAtmHCCellsTagged.description: High Capacity counter for the number of cells that were tagged

cpwAtmAvgCellsPacked.name: cpwAtmAvgCellsPacked
cpwAtmAvgCellsPacked.description: It indicates the Average number of cells that were received in one packet.

cpwAtmPktsReceived.name: cpwAtmPktsReceived
cpwAtmPktsReceived.description: This object can be used to obtain the information on the number of packets that were received and sent to the PSN.

cpwAtmPktsSent.name: cpwAtmPktsSent
cpwAtmPktsSent.description: This object indicates the number of packets that were sent to the atm network.

cpwAtmPktsRejected.name: cpwAtmPktsRejected
cpwAtmPktsRejected.description: This object indicates the number of packets that were rejected because of Policing.

cpwVcAtmModuleCompliance.name: cpwVcAtmModuleCompliance
cpwVcAtmModuleCompliance.description: The compliance statement for agent that support PW ATM.

cpwVcAtmGroup.name: cpwVcAtmGroup
cpwVcAtmGroup.description: Collection of objects for basic ATM PW outbound config.

cpwAtmPerfGroup.name: cpwAtmPerfGroup
cpwAtmPerfGroup.description: Collection of objects counting various outbound ATM PW statistics.
